import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Fibreglass Pools Gold Coast | Aqua-Tech, Compass, Leisure Pools | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Fibreglass swimming pool installation on the Gold Coast — premium shells from Aqua-Tech, Compass, Leisure Pools, Narellan. 3-5 week install. Colour-stable 25+ years. QBCC-licensed.">
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://goldcoastpoolbuilders.com.au/services/fibreglass-pools/">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Pre-formed shells &middot; fast install &middot; long life</span>
      <h1>Fibreglass pools across the <span class="accent">Gold Coast</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Aqua-Tech, Compass, Leisure Pools and Narellan fibreglass shells &mdash;
        manufactured offsite, craned into the excavation, plumbed and commissioned
        in 3&ndash;5 weeks total. Colour-stable for 25+ years with no resurface
        needed. Best for narrow beachside blocks, fast turnaround, and
        budget-conscious family pools.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free on-site quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Fibreglass shell brands we install.</h2>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Compass Pools (QLD-built):</strong> Vantage and Ceramic core construction with 7-layer gel coat. 5m&ndash;12m shells. Lifetime structural warranty. Premium price ($45K&ndash;$70K installed).</li>
          <li><strong>Aqua-Technics:</strong> Perth-built, distributed nationally. Hybrid Composite Construction (HCC). 4m&ndash;12m shells. 35-year structural warranty. ~$38K&ndash;$58K installed.</li>
          <li><strong>Leisure Pools:</strong> Multi-layer gel coat with Composite Armour. 6m&ndash;13m shells. 25-year warranty. ~$35K&ndash;$55K installed.</li>
          <li><strong>Narellan:</strong> Quality budget option. Standard gel coat. 5m&ndash;10m shells. 20-year warranty. ~$32K&ndash;$48K installed.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Standard shell sizes (most popular).</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Plunge pool 3.5&ndash;4.5m:</strong> Tiny block, side yard, courtyard. Family of 2&ndash;3. $30K&ndash;$42K.</li>
          <li><strong>Mid-family 6&ndash;7m:</strong> Most common. Suits 500&ndash;700m&sup2; suburban block. Family of 3&ndash;5. $38K&ndash;$55K.</li>
          <li><strong>Large family 8&ndash;9m:</strong> Larger rear yards. Real swimming length. $48K&ndash;$65K.</li>
          <li><strong>Lap-style 10&ndash;12m:</strong> Long narrow shell, serious swimmer. Often paired with spa. $55K&ndash;$78K.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Why fibreglass works on the Gold Coast.</h3>
        <p>
          Fibreglass is the right answer for most Gold Coast residential pool
          installs, for four reasons:
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Speed.</strong> 3&ndash;5 weeks excavation to swim. Concrete equivalents take 10&ndash;16 weeks.</li>
          <li><strong>Cost.</strong> 30&ndash;50% cheaper than concrete-equivalent build.</li>
          <li><strong>Salt resistance.</strong> Gel-coat surface is inert to salt-chlorinator water &mdash; no surface attack like pebble suffers.</li>
          <li><strong>Resurface-free.</strong> No 12&ndash;20 year resurface cycle. The gel coat holds for 25+ years before colour fade matters.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">When fibreglass is the WRONG answer.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Irregular shape required.</strong> Fibreglass is mould-formed &mdash; you pick from the brand&rsquo;s catalogue. Need a true freeform curve? Concrete.</li>
          <li><strong>Length over 12m.</strong> Maximum standard mould is 12m. Lap pools above that = concrete.</li>
          <li><strong>Block access blocked.</strong> Shell needs to crane in or come through a side gate. Established palm or 1.5m gap = problem. Sometimes solved with helicopter delivery (+$5K&ndash;$10K).</li>
          <li><strong>Architectural high-end.</strong> Knife-edge weirs, full-tile interior, dark beach-entry tiles &mdash; fibreglass doesn&rsquo;t do these convincingly. Concrete.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Install timeline (typical 7m shell).</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Day 1&ndash;2:</strong> Excavation + dewatering if needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Day 3:</strong> Bed sand layer, shell delivery, crane install, level.</li>
          <li><strong>Day 4&ndash;6:</strong> Plumbing rough-in (suction, return, drain, skimmer).</li>
          <li><strong>Day 7&ndash;10:</strong> Backfill, coping, equipment installation.</li>
          <li><strong>Day 11&ndash;15:</strong> Fill, commission, water balance, surround paving.</li>
          <li><strong>Day 16&ndash;21:</strong> Glass fence, Form 23 inspection, handover.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

